Instead of $pull use $addToSet.
$addToSet will create the array field with the specified value.
Here a link to the mongodb doc [addToSet][1]
```
import { Meteor } from &#39;meteor/meteor&#39;;
import { Mongo } from &#39;meteor/mongo&#39;;

Meteor.methods({
   &#39;agentPageAccess&#39;({userID, pageID}) {
      Pages.update({ &quot;PageID&quot; : pageID }, {
        $addToSet: { &quot;agentAccess&quot; : { &quot;agentID&quot; : userID } }
      });   
    }
});
```


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/update/addToSet/

